Types of Programming Language : 
    a. Low Level Language
        |-- Binary Language 
            |-Advantages
                i. instructions are given in the form of 0's and 1's 
                ii. Processing speed is fast
                iii. Execution time is less 
                iv. Machine Language
            |-DisAdvantages
                i. Programmers are not able to memorize code
                ii. Updation and Debugging is difficult 
                iii. Time Consuming

        |-- Assembly Language
            |-Advantages
                i. instructions are given in alpha numeric symbols (Mnemonic code)
                    ADD for Addition, SUB for subtraction, MUL for multiplication etc
                    CPY, CMP, MOV etc
                ii. Here we need Assembler as a translator
                    Assembly Language <--------Assembler---------> Machine Language 
                iii. Mainly used in Processors 

            |-DisAdvantages
                i. It is not a portable language 
                ii. Machine dependent 
                iii. Time Consuming 
                iv. One line of Assembly language is converted into multiple lines of machine code. 

                    ADD A,B   --------->   5 = 1010010101
                                           6 = 0101010101
                                        ADD  = 0001110001
                                               1010101010    

    b. Middle Level Language
        |-- C, C++
            English like statements<---- instructions
            Compiler as a translator

    c. High Level Language
        |-- Java, Python, .Net etc

        i. instructions are given in English like statements 
        ii. Updation is easier as compared to above two languages 
        iii.  Debugging is also easier as compared to above two languages
        iv. It is a portable language 
        v. Machine Independent 
        vi. Here we use compiler and interpreter as a translator